Hi Guys, For a contact, the custom property 'main deal record id' (indicating the most recently associated deal) was updated to `XXXXXXXX016` on *July 10th*, replacing the previous ID, `XXXXXXXX826`. However, when an order was associated with this contact on *October 16th*, my workflow’s custom code should have retrieved the latest 'main deal record ID'  to associate with the order. But when I retrieved it via the API, it returned `XXXXXXXX826` instead. Any idea why this discrepancy occurred?

here is my code FYI

const getContactDealId = async (contactId) => {
  try {
    const response = await HubSpotClient.crm.contacts.basicApi.getById(contactId,['main_deal_record_id'])

    return response.properties?.main_deal_record_id;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error fetching contact:', error.message);
    return null;
  }
};
